The paper deals with embedding knowledge graphs into real-valued tensors and using them for predicting new facts. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of prior background knowledge and the extraction of knowledge from existing graphs, which are topics related to databases (cs.DB). The task of predicting new facts involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and the evaluation of the models' performance, which can be considered as a form of system evaluation (cs.SI).
